| The 660 Gallon Brewery Fuel Cell                                   |
|   from the drinking-electricity dept.                              |
|   posted by samzenpus on Wednesday May 02, @20:48 (Power)          |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/02/2241250      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

An anonymous reader writes "Australia's University of Queensland has
secured a $115,000 grant for a 660-gallon fuel cell that should produce 2
kilowatts of power. A [0]prototype has been operating at the university
laboratory for three months. This fuel cell type is essentially a battery
in which bacteria consume water-soluble brewing waste such as sugar,
starch and alcohol, plus in this instance produces clean water."

Discuss this story at:
    http://science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/05/02/2241250

