|   http://slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/03/0350244              |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]AlHunt writes "A fire started by a homeless man [1]knocked out service
between Boston and New York on the experimental Internet2 network Tuesday
night. Authorities say the fire, which also disrupted service on the Red
Line subway, started around 8:20 p.m. when a homeless man tossed a lit
cigarette. The cigarette landed on a mattress, which ignited and led to a
two-alarm fire."

