| Bridging the Gap Between Hackers and Academics                     |
|   from the black-hats-in-gowns dept.                               |
|   posted by kdawson on Thursday May 03, @13:11 (Security)          |
|   http://it.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/03/1512202           |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]Tal Garfinkel writes "There has long been a disconnect between
academic computer security and underground forums like Black Hat and
Phrack. A new USENIX-sponsored workshop called [1]WOOT (Workshop On
Offensive Technologies) is looking to bridge that gap by providing a
high-quality, peer-reviewed forum for attack papers, with top reviewers
from the academic, open source, commercial IT, and information warfare
communities. Got a great attack paper? [2]See if it makes the cut at WOOT."

