+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Mercury May Have Molten Hot Magma at its Core                      |
|   from the but-no-ragnaros dept.                                   |
|   posted by CowboyNeal on Thursday May 03, @19:21 (NASA)           |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/03/2239250      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]mattatwork writes "According to ScienceDaily, NASA has come to the
conclusion that the planet [1]Mercury may have a molten core after all,
based on high-precision planetary radar readings. You may (or may not)
remember the [2]Mariner 10 probe making 3 passes by Mercury between March
29th, 1974, September 21st 1974 and March 16, 1975."

